DUBAI: US singer Demi Lovato will perform in Dubai at the Coca-Cola Arena on March 18, it was announced on Thursday morning. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The “Cool For The Summer” hitmaker will no doubt take to the stage with a number of popular songs from her repertoire, including “Skyscraper” and “Sorry Not Sorry.” A post shared by Full Circle Presents (@fullcirclepresents) Tickets for the event are on sale now, with prices at $53 (bronze), $75 (silver), $81 (standing), $109 (gold) and $136 (golden circle). Tickets are available at coca-cola-arena.etixdubai.com. In September, Lovato said that her latest tour, in support of her eighth studio album, will be her last.